  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting social justice towards our common home</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This initiative aims to promote the social justice of Salvadoran citizens seeking to adopt an integral ecology approach through action, accompaniment and education in human rights issues. As expressed in the Encyclical Laudato Si &quot;an integral ecology is inseparable from the notion of the common good, a central and unifying principle of social ethics. The common good is the sum of those conditions of social life which allow social groups and their individual members relatively thorough and ready access to their own fulfilment&#x201D; (# 156). For the partner &quot;Is this common good to which in our political systems aspire that all citizens enjoy all the rights that emanate from it.&quot; The main issue that the project will address is the lack of justice to victims of the armed conflict in El Salvador not only related to specific cases accompanied by the Partner but also advocating for public policies and measures to guarantee a national system for truth, justice, reparation and no repetition. At the same time, the root causes of the  violence in the country will be analysed within educational and advocacy processes  with vulnerable groups (young people, women and indigenous communities) to increase the awareness and citizen participation to achieve changes in the national and local structures. 

In the context of the COVID-19 pandemic, the main project activities have been maintained and appropriate adaptations were held.</narrative>
  </description>
